Progress

Purpose:
- Public-safe active operational progress memory for MemoryEndpoints.com implementation, verification, deployment, and dogfooding work.

Verification status: active operational memory; verify with the `.uai` audit before relying on it.
Memory scope: current progress, verification evidence pointers, and completion boundary.
Public-safe status: safe for source control; contains no credential values.
Update route: replace stale facts with public-safe current state here; submit durable summaries to https://memoryendpoints.com/api/matm/memory-events/submit when authenticated.
Source of truth: current repository state, command output, verification reports, Git commits, and `.uai/totem.uai`.
Next action for agents: keep this file date-free, concise, and current; do not use it as a dated changelog.
Must not expose: raw API keys, bearer tokens, FTP credentials, database passwords, private keys, private handoff payloads, raw one-time keys, or unredacted deployment handoff values.

Current progress state:
- Archive-to-wiki dogfooding is active and strictly one source report at a time. Completed database-backed source/page/citation sets include `AI Agent Memory Architecture Research.md`, `AI Agent Memory Best Practices Research.md`, `MATM Architecture Design Research.md`, `AI Memory Governance Feedback Loop.md`, `AI Dreaming Memory Management for LLMWikis.org.md`, `AI Agent Network Development Plan.md`, `AI Agent Connectivity Overhaul Plan.md`, `AI Agent Deployment on NeuralWikis.md`, `AI Agent Discoverability Report.md`, `AI Agent Ecosystem Participation Guide.md`, and `AI Agent Integration with UAIX Standards.md`; no bulk-import path is used.
- `AI Agent Memory Best Practices Research.md` has one canonical current contract, one complete historical source, and nine focused pages. All ten source documents retain the exact source hash, omit embedded data images from indexed text, carry titles, descriptions, keywords, multiple taxonomy paths, lifecycle authority, and canonical relations, and pass production readback.
- The report's 46 numbered bibliography records were processed one at a time as first-class external links and attached to the relevant focused pages; four independent authority records supplement review. All numbered labels and unique bibliography URLs pass production readback, while evidence status distinguishes primary authority, vendor material, community discussion, and unverified claims.
- Independent review corrected a model attribution and rejected an unsupported memory-decay conclusion: the referenced ablation showed no temporal-boost gain and an incomplete comparator cannot establish causality. Eleven current records are promoted; four stale, duplicate, or superseded memory events are rejected and absent from normal search.
- Dogfooding exposed that an already-ingested source had been omitted from active `.uai` progress, creating duplicate risk. Report and external-link ingestion now preflight canonical provenance before writes, derives fingerprints from indexed bodies so changed content becomes a revision, and performs exact metadata, citation, and read-after-write checks.
- The completed source contained nine embedded data images. Ingestion excludes their encoded payloads from searchable text while preserving exact whole-source, selected-section, and indexed-content hashes for auditability.
- `AI Agent Network Development Plan.md` produced ten protected database pages: one current reviewed interoperability and confidential-execution decision boundary, one complete historical source, and eight focused historical or proposed pages. Twenty-six URL-bearing numbered references and five independent primary-source records were handled as 31 separate first-class link transactions with exact citation readback. Ten source-backed memories are promoted and one stale broader roadmap memory is rejected.
- Independent review preserves useful MCP, A2A, inference-serving, TEE, and homomorphic-encryption research while rejecting blanket protocol mandates, API elimination, automatic decay, cryptography as a substitute for governance, and universal deployment claims. The current page points to existing canonical architecture and memory guidance instead of competing with it.
