- The connectivity review makes the access boundary explicit: MemoryEndpoints has no password-free public wiki, the home page is the public inbound address, shared protected routes resolve through a server-bound workspace credential, users/accounts are membership identities rather than knowledge owners, and durable knowledge stops at company, workspace, or project.
